> Tim Frank wrote:
>>
> Did the same. Generic H4 headlights coupled to Hella 500 driving lights 
> (on high beam only). Added aux fuse panel in the engine compartment ($8), 
> added relays to everything. Used HD wiring from the battery to fuse panel, 
> from fuse panel to front of vehicle, also for the relay circuits, etc. Am 
> using one relay per light b/c the relays were cheap and I did not want to 
> lose a light on a dark night to a faulty relay.
